        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The testing library provides two protocols, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/CustomTestStringConvertible",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "CustomTestReflectable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", that you can use to customize the appearance of",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "values in Swift. The testing library uses these protocols to describe",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "parameterized test arguments and, if a call to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/expect(_:_:sourceLocation:)",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/require(_:_:sourceLocation:)-5l63q",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " fails, to describe any values you pass",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "to them.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Customize-the-description-of-a-value",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Customize the description of a value",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You use the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/CustomTestStringConvertible",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " protocol when you want to customize",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the description of a value ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "during testing only",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". Values whose types conform to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "this protocol use it to describe themselves when the testing library presents",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "them as part of the output of a test. For example, this protocol affects the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "display of values you pass as arguments to test functions or that are elements",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "of an expectation failure.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "By default, the testing library converts values to strings using",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/string\/init(describing:)-67ncf",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The resulting string may be inappropriate for some types and their values. If",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "you make the type of the value conform to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/CustomTestStringConvertible",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", then",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the testing library will use the value of its ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/CustomTestStringConvertible\/testDescription",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "property instead.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For example, consider the following type:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "enum Food: CaseIterable {",
            "  case paella, oden, ragu",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you pass an array of cases from this enumeration to a parameterized test",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "function:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "@Test(arguments: Food.allCases)",
            "func isDelicious(_ food: Food) { ... }"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Then the testing library needs to present all elements in the array in its",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "output, but the default description of these values may not be adequately",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "descriptive:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "◇ Test case passing 1 argument food → .paella to isDelicious(_:) started.",
            "◇ Test case passing 1 argument food → .oden to isDelicious(_:) started.",
            "◇ Test case passing 1 argument food → .ragu to isDelicious(_:) started."
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When you adopt ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/CustomTestStringConvertible",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", you can include customized",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "descriptions in your test output instead.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "extension Food: CustomTestStringConvertible {",
            "  var testDescription: String {",
            "    switch self {",
            "    case .paella:",
            "      \"paella valenciana\"",
            "    case .oden:",
            "      \"おでん\"",
            "    case .ragu:",
            "      \"ragù alla bolognese\"",
            "    }",
            "  }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The testing library then uses ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/CustomTestStringConvertible\/testDescription",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "present these values:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "◇ Test case passing 1 argument food → paella valenciana to isDelicious(_:) started.",
            "◇ Test case passing 1 argument food → おでん to isDelicious(_:) started.",
            "◇ Test case passing 1 argument food → ragù alla bolognese to isDelicious(_:) started."
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Customize-the-reflection-of-a-value",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Customize the reflection of a value",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When a call to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/expect(_:_:sourceLocation:)",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/require(_:_:sourceLocation:)-5l63q",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "fails, the testing library presents the value or values you pass to these macros",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "in its output.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The testing library uses ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/mirror\/init(reflecting:)",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "to break down these values if they contain properties that may be of interest to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "you. For instance, if the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "isDelicious(_:)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " test fails, you might see output",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "such as:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "✘ Test isDelicious(_:) recorded an issue with 1 argument food → sandwich",
            "↳ food.isDelicious → false",
            "↳   food → sandwich",
            "↳     sandwich → (toppings: [Food.pickles, Food.candyCorn])",
            "↳       toppings → [Food.pickles, Food.candyCorn]",
            "↳   isDelicious → false"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This output is expressive, but also contains redundant information. You can",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "refine it further by making ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Food",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " conform to the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "CustomTestReflectable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "protocol.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "extension Food: CustomTestReflectable {",
            "  var customTestMirror: Mirror {",
            "    switch self {",
            "    case let .sandwich(toppings):",
            "      let ingredientNames = toppings.map { String(describingForTest: $0) }",
            "      return Mirror(",
            "        self,",
            "        children: [(label: \"toppings\", value: ingredientNames)]",
            "      )",
            "    default:",
            "      Mirror(self, children: [])",
            "    }",
            "  }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "With this conformance, the output of the failed test is instead:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "✘ Test isDelicious(_:) recorded an issue with 1 argument food → sandwich",
            "↳ food.isDelicious → false",
            "↳   food → sandwich",
            "↳     toppings → [\"pickles\", \"candy corn\"]",
            "↳   isDelicious → false"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Implement-custom-descriptions-using-private-properties",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Implement custom descriptions using private properties",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If part or all of your type’s state is ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "private",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or otherwise not visible to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "your test target, you may not be able to implement ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/CustomTestStringConvertible\/testDescription",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "CustomTestReflectable\/customTestMirror",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in your test target. You can",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "implement these properties, without adding conformances to either protocol, in",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "your production target, and then add empty protocol conformances in your test",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "target. Make sure to use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "internal",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "package",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " visibility for the properties",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "so that your test target is able to use them.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
